{{Use mdy dates|date=March 2015}} {{Infobox person | name = Giuliana Rancic | image = Giuliana Rancic at the Time 100 Gala.jpg | image_size = 220px | caption = Rancic at the [[Time 100|''Time'' 100]] gala in May 2010 | birth_name = Giuliana DePandi | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1974|8|17}} | birth_place = [[Naples]], [[Italy]] | alma_mater = {{plain list| * [[University of Maryland, College Park]] * [[American University]] }} | occupation = Television personality | years_active = 1998–present | television = {{plain list| * ''[[E! News]]'' * ''[[Giuliana and Bill]]'' * ''[[Fashion Police]]'' }} | spouse = {{marriage|[[Bill Rancic]]|2007}} | children = 1 | website = {{URL|giulianarancic.com}} }} '''Giuliana Rancic''' (née '''DePandi''';<ref>{{cite web|people=Giuliana Rancic |url=http://scoop.today.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2011/12/05/9221432-giuliana-rancic-to-have-double-mastectomy?chromedomain=entertainment |title=Giuliana Rancic to have double mastectomy |medium=Television production |publisher=''[[Today (NBC program)|Today]]'' via MSNBC.com |location=4:59 of 6:11 clip |date=December 5, 2011 |quote=When they first told me mastectomy was an option I said absolutely not, absolutely not, I am 37 years old, I don't want to do that. |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111205224605/http://scoop.today.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2011/12/05/9221432-giuliana-rancic-to-have-double-mastectomy?chromedomain=entertainment |archivedate=December 5, 2011 |deadurl=yes |df=mdy }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20551166,00.html |title=Giuliana and Bill Rancic Thank Fans for Prayers|first=Rennie|last= Dyball|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=December 5, 2011 | archivedate= October 31, 2014| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141031103932/http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20551166,00.html | deadurl= no}}</ref> born August 17, 1974)<ref name=tvg>{{cite web | url = http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/giuliana-rancic-300806/bio/ | title= Giuliana Rancic | work= [[TV Guide]] | accessdate= February 24, 2015 | archivedate= February 24, 2015 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150224193420/http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/giuliana-rancic-300806/bio/| deadurl=no}}</ref> is an [[Italian-American]] television personality.
==Early life== Rancic was born in [[Naples]], [[Italy]] and immigrated to the United States with her family at age seven.<ref name=tvg /> She had surgery to correct her [[scoliosis]] during her late teens. In 1996,<ref name=tvg /> she received a [[bachelor's degree]] in [[journalism]] from the [[University of Maryland, College Park]], and a [[master's degree]] in journalism from [[American University]].<ref name=officialsite /> During this time, she worked for a [[Capitol Hill]] news bureau covering stories related to the U.S. government.<ref name=officialsite>{{official website|http://www.giulianarancic.com/|Giuliana Rancic}} (official site).</ref> Rancic also graduated from [[Barbizon Modeling and Acting School]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Barbizon Modeling and Acting School Alumni|url= http://www.barbizonmodeling.com/index.php/alumni/giuliana_rancic|publisher =Barbizon International | archivedate= November 26, 2014 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20141126122154/http://www.barbizonmodeling.com/index.php/alumni/giuliana_rancic | deadurl=no}}</ref>
==Career== In 2005, Rancic was named anchor of [[E!]] network's ''[[E! News]]''. On March 13, 2006, she was joined by co-anchor [[Ryan Seacrest]].{{citation needed|date=February 2015}}
Additionally, she co-hosts E!'s ''[[Fashion Police]]'' and often co-hosts [[red carpet]] events for award shows, such as the [[Golden Globes]] and the [[Academy Awards]]. She is the creator and executive producer of MTV's ''[[Celebrity Rap Superstar]]'', which premiered in 2007. She and her husband, [[Bill Rancic]], star in the [[reality-television]] show ''[[Giuliana and Bill]]'' which aired on E!. She appeared in the movie ''[[Bring It On: Fight to the Finish]]'' in a brief scene. Rancic also has hosted the [[Miss USA]] and [[Miss Universe]] beauty pageants on NBC.{{citation needed|date=February 2015}}
Rancic won the 2014 [[Daytime Emmy]] Award for Fan Favorite.<ref name="Finn">{{cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/553233/giuliana-rancic-wins-the-2014-daytime-emmys-fan-favorite-award|title=Giuliana Rancic Wins the 2014 Daytime Emmys' Fan Favorite Award!|publisher=[[E!]]|date=June 22, 2014|accessdate=June 22, 2014|first=Natalie|last=Finn}}</ref>
In 2013, Giuliana launched her clothing line, G by Giuliana, on HSN, a hugely successful line on HSN.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Serpe|first1=Gina|title=Giuliana Rancic Launches New Clothing Line, Puts Joan Rivers on Notice!|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/314561/giuliana-rancic-launches-new-clothing-line-puts-joan-rivers-on-notice|website=E! Online|publisher=E! Entertainment Television|accessdate=3 August 2015}}</ref> She also launched a wine line, Xo, G.<ref name="Xo, G">{{cite web | url=http://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/big-dreamer-landed-giuliana-rancic-wine-line/story?id=25576633 | author=Rothman, Michael | title=How Being a Big Dreamer Landed Giuliana Rancic Her Own Wine Line | work=Good Morning America | date=September 18, 2014 | accessdate=November 18, 2014}}</ref>
In 2013, Rancic, who has a history of breast cancer, founded Fab-U-Wish, a charity that grants wishes to women undergoing breast cancer treatment.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Toomey|first1=Alyssa|title=Giuliana Rancic Teams Up With Nonprofit Bright Pink for Fab-U-Wish™ Initiative to Help Women Battling Breast and Ovarian Cancer|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/396584/giuliana-rancic-teams-up-with-nonprofit-bright-pink-for-fab-u-wish-initiative-to-help-women-battling-breast-and-ovarian-cancer|website=E! Online|publisher=E! Entertainment Television|accessdate=3 August 2015}}</ref>
In February 2015, Rancic faced backlash over her controversial comments about synthetic dreadlocks worn by [[Zendaya]] at the Oscars, remarking that the hair looked like it smelled of "patchouli and weed".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/tv/zendaya-blasts-giuliana-rancic-for-criticizing-her-oscars-dreadlocks/|title=Giuliana Rancic Clarifies Apology to Zendaya After Oscar Night Comments About Her Dreadlocks|date=February 24, 2015|work=Amanda Michelle Steiner|accessdate=June 21, 2017}}</ref>
On July 10, 2015, Rancic announced that after nearly a decade, she will be leaving her position as co-anchor on ''[[E! News]]'', yet she will continue to be the host of ''[[Fashion Police]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/674414/giuliana-rancic-leaving-e-news-as-day-to-day-anchor-will-continue-on-fashion-police-live-from-the-red-carpet|title=Giuliana Rancic Leaving E! News|work=E! Online|accessdate=July 21, 2015}}</ref>
On September 4, 2018, the personality returned to her anchor job behind the desk of [[E! News]] a year after [[Catt Sadler]]'s controversial exit.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/giuliana-rancic-returning-e-news-1120549|title=Giuliana Rancic Returning to 'E! News'|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-09-05|language=en}}</ref>
==Personal life== On December 15, 2006, Giuliana and [[Bill Rancic]] announced their engagement. They were married on September 1, 2007, in a ceremony on [[Capri]] at Sancta Sophia Church in [[Anacapri]].<ref name="people">{{cite web |title=Apprentice's Bill Rancic, E!'s Giuliana DePandi To Wed|first=Mark |last=Dagostino|date=December 16, 2006 |work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20004416,00.html |accessdate=January 23, 2007}}</ref><ref>[http://www.eonline.com/news/article/index.jsp?uuid=3f16227f-8f56-4d0e-9ecb-81a7c673014a&page=1 E! News – You're Squired: E!'s Giuliana Weds Apprentice's Bill – Donald J Trump | Ryan Seacrest]{{failed verification|date=June 2015}}</ref>
The two have publicly discussed their fertility issues on television talk shows, having tried to conceive since approximately the beginning of 2009.<ref name="in vitro">{{cite web | url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b168892_giuliana_bill_rancic_share_in_vitro.html | author=Cady, Jennifer | title=Giuliana & Bill Rancic Share In Vitro Struggle | publisher=E! | date=February 25, 2010 | accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref> The couple began [[in vitro fertilization]] (IVF) in March 2010,<ref name="in vitro"/> and Rancic got pregnant in the spring of 2010, but she miscarried at nine weeks.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b203222_Bill_and_Giuliana_Rancic__We_Had_a_Miscarriage.html|author=Errico, Marcus|title=Bill and Giuliana Rancic: We Had a Miscarriage|publisher=E!|date=September 30, 2010|accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b203375_Giuliana_Rancic_Opens_Up_About_Her_Miscarriage.html|title=Giuliana Rancic Opens Up About Her Miscarriage|publisher=E!|date=September 30, 2010|accessdate=October 16, 2010}}</ref> She had an IVF transfer for a second time in November 2010; however, the procedure did not result in a pregnancy. When the couple decided to try for a third round of IVF, her doctor recommended a [[mammogram]], which is how she found out she had breast cancer. Despite her condition, the couple were still motivated to have a baby, so they continued with the egg retrieval and found a surrogate.<ref>{{Cite episode|title=Last Chance|series=Giuliana & Bill|network=E! Entertainment Television|airdate=December 20, 2010}}</ref>
On October 17, 2011, during an interview on ''[[Today (NBC program)|Today]]'', Rancic announced she had been diagnosed with early stage [[breast cancer]], for which she would be treated with a double [[lumpectomy]], followed by radiation. She underwent surgery in mid-October 2011 and returned to work at E! News about a week later.<ref>{{cite news|title=Giuliana Rancic returns back to work at E! News just days after undergoing double lumpectomy|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/gossip/giuliana-rancic-returns-back-work-e-news-days-undergoing-double-lumpectomy-article-1.967914|newspaper=Daily News|location=New York|date=October 25, 2011|accessdate=November 3, 2011}}</ref> On December 5, 2011, Rancic disclosed she had decided to undergo a bilateral [[mastectomy]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Errico|first=Marcus|title=Giuliana Rancic Getting Double Mastectomy: "I Will Come Back a Better Woman"|url=http://uk.eonline.com/news/giuliana_rancic_getting_double/278192|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120721020030/http://uk.eonline.com/news/giuliana_rancic_getting_double/278192|dead-url=yes|archive-date=July 21, 2012|publisher=E!|accessdate=December 5, 2011|date=December 5, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.newsday.com/entertainment/celebrities/celebrities-who-ve-had-cancer-1.1495619|title=Celebrities who've had cancer|work=Newsday|access-date=2017-07-03}}</ref>
On April 23, 2012, Giuliana and Bill announced on ''The Today Show'' that they were expecting their first child, via gestational carrier, due in late summer.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20589362,00.html|title=Giuliana Rancic, Bill Rancic to Be Parents : People.com|work=PEOPLE.com|accessdate=July 21, 2015}}</ref> Their son was born in late August, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/338760/Giuliana-and-Bill-Rancic-Welcome-a-Baby-Boy|publisher=E! |title=Giuliana and Bill Rancic Welcome a Baby Boy!|date=August 29, 2012|author1=Finn, Natalie |author2=Nessif, Bruna}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/celebritology/post/giuliana-and-bill-rancic-have-a-son-leeann-rimes-seeks-treatment/2012/08/30/363e8676-f295-11e1-892d-bc92fee603a7_blog.html|title=Giuliana and Bill Rancic have a son; LeeAnn Rimes seeks treatment|website=Washington Post|access-date=2017-07-24}}</ref>
